WEBVTT

00:09.235 --> 00:10.968
("Bolero" by Pink Martini
playing)

00:41.066 --> 00:42.958
♪

00:56.873 --> 00:58.807
("O Christmas Tree" playing)

01:05.599 --> 01:08.308
No, sweetie.
That's a deadly glass ball

01:08.385 --> 01:10.644
that we hang
where babies can get it.

01:10.720 --> 01:13.655
See? Deadly glass ball?

01:17.602 --> 01:19.986
(coughs)

01:20.063 --> 01:21.488
-BART: Oh!
-LISA: Oh!

01:21.565 --> 01:23.248
(yowls)

01:26.087 --> 01:28.921
Huh? Todd Flanders?
How'd that get on our tree?

01:28.997 --> 01:31.873
Christmas is no time
to think about your neighbors.

01:31.950 --> 01:33.667
It's a very interesting story.

01:33.743 --> 01:36.837
A Christmas story
of failing and redemption.

01:36.913 --> 01:39.422
Isn't that
every Christmas story?

01:39.433 --> 01:42.926
A Christmas story of your
father's failing and redemption.

01:42.937 --> 01:44.553
Isn't that every Homer story?

01:44.629 --> 01:46.555
This one also has a secret room,

01:46.631 --> 01:48.941
and it's set
six years in the past.

01:49.017 --> 01:52.185
Oh, thank God
it's not the horrible present.

01:52.262 --> 01:53.520
What year did it happen?

01:53.597 --> 01:55.280
Oh, you know the year.

01:55.357 --> 01:58.233
The Oscar went to an overrated
movie that nobody remembers,

01:58.310 --> 02:00.110
Tom Brady won the Super Bowl

02:00.121 --> 02:01.945
and a public figure
had to apologize

02:01.956 --> 02:03.947
for saying something stupid.

02:03.958 --> 02:05.782
-Oh, that one.
-That year.

02:05.793 --> 02:07.742
Oh, yeah. Mm-hmm.
Remember it well.

02:07.819 --> 02:09.536
Okay. So, Homer and I

02:09.613 --> 02:12.372
were going
to the office Christmas party.

02:12.449 --> 02:15.458
<i> GRAMPA: I had just lost</i>
<i> my last adult tooth,</i>

02:15.469 --> 02:18.461
<i> -which they say</i>
<i> is worth thousands.</i>
<i> -MARGE: Grampa.</i>

02:18.472 --> 02:20.714
-This is my story.
-Fine.

02:20.790 --> 02:22.257
We were getting ready...

02:22.334 --> 02:25.093
Listen, before we go,
I want to ask you a favor.

02:25.170 --> 02:27.637
Don't drink at the office party.

02:27.648 --> 02:30.265
But then
it just becomes a meeting.

02:30.342 --> 02:33.435
I'm serious. I don't want you
embarrassing yourself at work.

02:33.511 --> 02:36.229
All right. I'll just drink soda.

02:36.306 --> 02:38.991
-Water is healthier.
-Not in this town.

02:40.068 --> 02:43.737
Woo-hoo! Kids, get the hot dogs!

02:43.813 --> 02:46.239
Homer, that's not safe.

02:46.316 --> 02:48.584
(chuckles):
Marge, it's<i> natural</i> gas.

02:52.489 --> 02:54.464
-♪
-(indistinct chatter)

03:00.923 --> 03:03.465
Marge. Marge,
Marge, Marge, Marge.

03:03.541 --> 03:06.259
-When will you ever settle down?
-What the...?

03:06.336 --> 03:09.971
Hey, Marge,
want to rub shoulders?

03:10.048 --> 03:12.849
Cover yourself up
and quit hitting on my wife.

03:12.860 --> 03:15.027
Oh, so now she's<i> your</i> wife.

03:15.103 --> 03:17.529
I've never been at a party
where I'm sober

03:17.606 --> 03:20.032
and everyone else is drunk.
This is a nightmare.

03:20.108 --> 03:21.483
I know how you feel, pal.

03:21.559 --> 03:23.318
I haven't had a drink
in four years.

03:23.395 --> 03:25.779
You're so boring.

03:25.855 --> 03:28.081
He's right. I<i> am</i> boring.

03:30.285 --> 03:32.377
We should give Homer
a little help

03:32.454 --> 03:34.213
-enjoying the party.
-Mm-hmm.

03:37.960 --> 03:41.294
So, if you're all partying,
who's running the plant?

03:41.371 --> 03:44.631
We got a dog that barks
when a light goes red.

03:44.708 --> 03:46.350
(beeping)

03:48.395 --> 03:51.104
(yawns)

04:03.151 --> 04:05.869
Ah, it's nice to get close
to the workers once a year.

04:07.564 --> 04:10.082
-Are you enjoying your holiday?
-I was just watching

04:10.158 --> 04:12.534
this fantastic movie,
<i> It's a Wonderful Life.</i>

04:12.610 --> 04:14.253
A tribute
to my favorite character:

04:14.329 --> 04:17.497
the conniving, evil banker
who ruins Christmas Eve.

04:17.574 --> 04:20.425
I presume it ends
with Jimmy Stewart's suicide.

04:20.502 --> 04:22.252
Attention! Attention!

04:22.263 --> 04:25.588
I've arranged for some of
the latest hip music to be sung.

04:25.599 --> 04:29.342
♪<i> Hark, the herald angels sing</i> ♪

04:29.419 --> 04:33.179
♪<i> Good old Monty is our king</i> ♪

04:33.256 --> 04:36.891
♪<i> He's a mean old crocodile</i> ♪

04:36.968 --> 04:40.895
♪<i> Worse than jock itch</i>
<i> by a mile</i> ♪

04:40.972 --> 04:44.616
♪<i> I can't wait</i>
<i> till Burnsy dies</i> ♪

04:44.693 --> 04:48.737
♪<i> Watching vultures</i>
<i> eat his eyes.</i> ♪

04:48.813 --> 04:51.531
Not so fast. Release the hounds!

04:51.608 --> 04:55.285
On, Slasher! On, Gasher!
On, Mangey and Nips 'Em!

04:55.296 --> 04:58.955
On, Stalker! On, Vicious!
On, Rabid and Rips 'Em!

04:58.966 --> 05:00.757
(hounds growl)

05:07.332 --> 05:09.766
Good night, Mr. Burns.

05:14.172 --> 05:16.973
Die! Die! Die!

05:16.984 --> 05:19.559
And cool me whiskey.

05:19.636 --> 05:20.968
(people screaming)

05:21.046 --> 05:24.397
♪<i> Good King Wenceslas</i>
<i> looked out.</i> ♪

05:24.474 --> 05:26.566
(harmonized scream)

05:26.643 --> 05:28.735
Homer, we've got to go.

05:28.812 --> 05:31.654
Come on, can't I finish
filling my pants with shrimp?

05:31.665 --> 05:33.165
Mm.

05:33.241 --> 05:35.450
Ooh.

05:35.527 --> 05:37.294
(siren wailing)

05:39.340 --> 05:40.580
I don't know what happened.

05:40.657 --> 05:43.083
What happened
is what happens every time.

05:43.159 --> 05:46.053
You got drunk,
and you made a fool of yourself.

05:47.372 --> 05:48.680
(sobs softly)

05:48.757 --> 05:51.016
I don't want you coming home

05:51.093 --> 05:53.393
until I know you've changed.

05:54.879 --> 05:56.638
Good night.

05:56.714 --> 05:59.024
Uh, aren't you gonna get out?

05:59.101 --> 06:02.519
No, just drive me around
in circles, please.

06:02.529 --> 06:06.323
Oh, sorry. You have to order
an Uber Sad for that.

06:10.278 --> 06:13.372
There, there. Prices
are always surging at Christmas.

06:13.448 --> 06:16.541
Where do I go? Where do I go?

06:16.618 --> 06:19.702
Hey. You got to bowl or go home.

06:19.713 --> 06:22.122
♪ ♪

06:22.198 --> 06:23.548
Skate or go home.

06:25.460 --> 06:28.044
Go home or go home.

06:28.055 --> 06:30.630
Isn't a church
supposed to offer sanctuary?

06:30.707 --> 06:33.508
I'll tell you what.
Quote one Bible verse,

06:33.585 --> 06:35.677
and I'll let you in.

06:35.753 --> 06:38.346
Um... "There once was a man
from Judaea

06:38.423 --> 06:41.057
who said to my wife,
'If I pay ya...'"

06:41.068 --> 06:42.225
And no.

06:42.236 --> 06:44.561
Please. I have nowhere to go.

06:44.571 --> 06:47.355
Well, there is one person

06:47.432 --> 06:49.858
that takes the homeless,
lost dogs,

06:49.934 --> 06:52.953
even grocery bags
carried off by the wind.

06:54.063 --> 06:56.739
Oh. I don't know
how to put this.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.042
Come on in, my brother.

07:00.278 --> 07:01.920
You, too.

07:04.666 --> 07:07.208
Look, Maude. God blessed us
with another mouth

07:07.285 --> 07:09.594
-to feed.
-(scoffs)

07:09.671 --> 07:11.254
More like a sinkhole
that likes french fries.

07:11.265 --> 07:13.598
Oh, now, Maude, Jesus said,
"Love your neighbor"

07:13.675 --> 07:16.384
even though he never seemed
to live next to anyone.

07:16.461 --> 07:19.429
Please, Ned. I'm due any day.

07:19.440 --> 07:22.441
Maude, when I look
in that man's face, I see Jesus.

07:22.517 --> 07:24.651
When you look at everything,
you see Jesus.

07:25.762 --> 07:28.021
I bet you're seeing Jesus
right now.

07:28.097 --> 07:29.731
I love you so much.

07:29.807 --> 07:31.357
Put him in your man cave.

07:31.434 --> 07:32.525
Man cave?

07:32.602 --> 07:34.619
My Son of Man cave.

07:34.696 --> 07:37.456
The Wi-Fi password is
"sinners burn in hell."

07:37.532 --> 07:39.699
The second "S" is a dollar sign.

07:39.776 --> 07:42.368
The first "L" is a one.
The "E" in "sinners" is a three,

07:42.445 --> 07:44.787
but the "E" in "hell"
is an "E" for "eternity."

07:44.798 --> 07:48.175
(groans) I'll just use
my data plan like an animal.

07:50.378 --> 07:52.462
(clattering)

07:52.473 --> 07:54.639
You ate the Christmas ham.

07:54.716 --> 07:56.716
And it wasn't even cooked.

07:56.793 --> 07:58.426
Wait, wait.
You were saving that?

07:58.503 --> 08:00.637
(exhales)
It was still in the plastic.

08:00.647 --> 08:03.097
That was plastic? Uh-oh.

08:03.174 --> 08:05.475
I know it's tough, Marge,

08:05.486 --> 08:06.893
but you're doing
the right thing.

08:06.970 --> 08:08.603
Just like I raised him.

08:08.680 --> 08:10.230
Punish, punish, punish.

08:10.306 --> 08:12.690
And after it's much too late,
love.

08:12.767 --> 08:14.493
It's not just this one thing.

08:14.569 --> 08:17.487
It's a pattern
of constant disappointment.

08:17.498 --> 08:20.949
You must see it.
You live with us temporarily.

08:21.025 --> 08:23.168
What do you mean, "temporarily"?

08:23.245 --> 08:25.286
Nothing. Nothing, nothing.

08:25.363 --> 08:26.880
Have a good night.

08:29.033 --> 08:30.675
(quiet whimpers)

08:32.996 --> 08:36.056
Oh, I can't take this place.

08:37.834 --> 08:38.591
Ooh!

08:38.668 --> 08:40.301
Aw.

08:40.378 --> 08:43.647
Even my peripheral vision
is betraying me.

08:48.720 --> 08:51.938
(snarls)

08:52.015 --> 08:56.034
So, wife threw you out, eh?

08:56.111 --> 08:59.696
-Yeah.
-We've got a nice,
warm bed for you

08:59.706 --> 09:02.374
in the lake of eternal flame!

09:02.450 --> 09:05.702
A house by the lake?
I could get some writing done.

09:05.712 --> 09:07.495
<i> In</i> the lake.

09:07.572 --> 09:10.373
Oh, thank God.
Any excuse not to write.

09:10.384 --> 09:12.592
(groans)
Kill me.

09:14.412 --> 09:15.962
<i> KRUSTY:</i>
<i> Hey, hey, kids.</i>

09:16.039 --> 09:17.297
<i> Especially the little ones.</i>

09:17.373 --> 09:19.215
<i> Here's an all-new</i>
Itchy & Scratchy.

09:19.226 --> 09:21.059
<i> Parental discretion advised.</i>

09:21.136 --> 09:23.803
<i> But if they were around,</i>
<i> you wouldn't be watching.</i>

09:23.880 --> 09:25.605
<i> (laughs)</i>

09:26.733 --> 09:27.607
<i> Ah!</i>

09:28.551 --> 09:29.901
<i> Ah!</i>

09:32.906 --> 09:34.063
<i> (screams)</i>

09:34.074 --> 09:35.565
(both scream)

09:35.576 --> 09:37.650
Where's Daddy?

09:37.727 --> 09:40.745
Um, he-he won't be back
for a while.

09:40.822 --> 09:43.072
It's okay. I love Bart.

09:43.083 --> 09:46.326
I love Bart.
I love Bart. I love Bart.

09:46.402 --> 09:48.253
And I love Lisa.

09:48.330 --> 09:50.538
BOTH:
I love you,
I love you, I love you.

09:50.615 --> 09:51.998
Oh, that's wonderful.

09:52.075 --> 09:54.876
We can still have
a nice Christmas,

09:54.952 --> 09:56.836
-even without your...
-(chuckles) Daddy's back.

09:56.913 --> 09:58.212
Daddy's back.

09:58.289 --> 10:00.715
Look at that hat.
He must be a millionaire.

10:00.792 --> 10:02.425
(both scream)

10:02.436 --> 10:04.102
Okay, it's time to go to bed.

10:04.179 --> 10:06.095
We'll have fun tomorrow.

10:06.106 --> 10:08.106
(both scream)

10:08.183 --> 10:10.391
("Jingle Bells" playing)

10:10.468 --> 10:14.863
See? Even without Daddy,
it's Christmas at the mall.

10:16.766 --> 10:18.858
Please give something.

10:18.935 --> 10:21.953
I'm about to be the first person
ever dishonorably discharged

10:22.030 --> 10:23.913
by the Salvation Army.

10:27.485 --> 10:30.128
Aw, that was a real beard.

10:32.448 --> 10:34.582
Can I get these
for me and Daddy?

10:34.659 --> 10:37.752
I'm not sure Daddy will be back
by Christmas.

10:37.829 --> 10:41.214
Ooh, I smell marital problems.

10:41.290 --> 10:42.965
A salesman's dream.

10:42.976 --> 10:45.218
Little boy,
if she doesn't buy it,

10:45.294 --> 10:47.220
she doesn't love you.

10:47.296 --> 10:50.390
Really? And do you have
a happy homelife?

10:50.466 --> 10:52.567
Why, ye-- No.

10:55.346 --> 10:57.656
Aw, poor fella.
I know what'll cheer him up.

10:57.732 --> 10:59.824
Homer, would you like
to say grace?

10:59.901 --> 11:01.776
I'd rather just eat.

11:01.853 --> 11:03.403
No grace?

11:03.479 --> 11:05.830
Then I'm gonna let
my hair grow natural.

11:05.907 --> 11:06.781
(hair pops)

11:06.858 --> 11:08.241
Homer, please.

11:08.317 --> 11:10.284
Honor the Lord
until we're all bored.

11:10.361 --> 11:11.494
(sighs)

11:11.505 --> 11:13.496
Dear God, how you doing?

11:13.507 --> 11:15.674
I know your son's
birthday's coming up.

11:15.750 --> 11:18.167
Oh, with his mother, you say?

11:18.178 --> 11:20.294
Oh, that's too bad.

11:20.371 --> 11:23.506
Now, Homer, in this house,
grace is personal, pious,

11:23.517 --> 11:25.133
and at least 500 words.

11:25.185 --> 11:26.467
Fine.

11:26.544 --> 11:28.520
Thank You, O Lord,
for my wonderful home,

11:28.596 --> 11:29.804
which I'm not in.

11:29.881 --> 11:32.691
And my beautiful family,
which I can't see.

11:32.767 --> 11:35.309
I mean,
Flanders is great and all,

11:35.386 --> 11:38.438
but even you must think
he's kind of a jackass.

11:38.514 --> 11:40.314
What's a jackass?

11:40.391 --> 11:42.033
It's a silly person, Roddy.

11:42.110 --> 11:44.110
Daddy, you're a jackass.

11:44.187 --> 11:46.204
Sheesh. The mouth on that kid.

11:46.281 --> 11:49.365
Ned, that man has got to go.

11:49.376 --> 11:51.543
Maude, you know we can't
turn away someone in need

11:51.619 --> 11:53.286
right before Christmas.

11:53.362 --> 11:55.496
You're right.
I forgot my Christian values.

11:55.573 --> 11:58.541
Could you please get our guest
some Christmas candy?

11:58.552 --> 12:00.552
Absotively.

12:02.464 --> 12:03.796
Get the hell out.

12:03.873 --> 12:05.056
(whimpers)

12:06.801 --> 12:08.059
Where'd he go?

12:08.136 --> 12:10.136
Can't be a rapture, I know that.

12:10.213 --> 12:12.063
-HOMER: Yep.
-Scram!

12:13.975 --> 12:15.817
I have no luck.

12:22.576 --> 12:24.066
Just keep bringing me drinks

12:24.077 --> 12:26.244
until I pass out
under this table.

12:26.321 --> 12:29.038
Also, you have tables?

12:32.068 --> 12:33.910
Why aren't you home with Midge?

12:33.920 --> 12:37.371
I've been kicked out.
I have no place to go.

12:37.448 --> 12:38.923
Oh, you poor guy.

12:39.000 --> 12:40.383
Let's take a walk.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.139
Finally.

12:52.939 --> 12:54.439
Aw...

12:54.516 --> 12:56.724
(groans)

12:56.801 --> 12:59.778
If only I could get back
in there tonight.

12:59.854 --> 13:01.687
Well, uh, actually,
there is a way.

13:01.764 --> 13:04.282
What are you talking about?

13:04.359 --> 13:07.109
There's a tiny little room
above your garage

13:07.120 --> 13:08.453
that you've never noticed.

13:08.530 --> 13:11.364
Until Marge forgives you,
you can hide out in there.

13:11.440 --> 13:13.908
Have you ever stayed up there?

13:13.985 --> 13:17.703
I haven't, but, uh, I did rent
it out to a nice Irish family.

13:17.780 --> 13:19.672
(sad flute melody plays)

13:21.450 --> 13:24.585
Oh, Ma, this is the best place
we've ever lived.

13:24.662 --> 13:27.630
We only have to clean
Moe's bar for seven years,

13:27.641 --> 13:29.599
and then we get
our passports back.

13:38.342 --> 13:40.568
("Silent Night" playing)

13:47.661 --> 13:49.702
♪

13:52.999 --> 13:56.075
LISA:
God bless Bart.
God bless Mommy.

13:56.152 --> 13:58.503
God bless Santa.
Santa bless God.

13:58.580 --> 14:01.956
And especially
God bless Daddy.

14:02.033 --> 14:04.166
BART:
God, I don't know
if you could do this,

14:04.177 --> 14:06.627
but I want a different father.

14:06.704 --> 14:09.097
(sobs) I'm home.

14:15.763 --> 14:17.480
("Carol of the Bells" playing)

14:34.708 --> 14:36.207
(music fades)

14:36.242 --> 14:39.201
So cozy. Ooh, cheese!

14:39.212 --> 14:40.703
Rat trap! Ow!

14:40.714 --> 14:42.204
Ooh, more cheese.

14:42.215 --> 14:44.206
Rat trap! Ow!

14:44.217 --> 14:45.625
Ooh, rat trap!

14:45.701 --> 14:47.919
Cheese! Ow!

14:47.995 --> 14:51.047
At least I haven't seen
any spiders.

14:51.057 --> 14:55.551
Cool. Now that I'm a bachelor
again, my hair is coming back.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.228
Aah!

15:00.383 --> 15:01.399
(phone rings)

15:04.070 --> 15:05.061
Hey, Lenny.

15:05.071 --> 15:07.021
Yeah, I'm doing okay.

15:07.098 --> 15:09.073
You're living the life
you always dreamed of:

15:09.150 --> 15:10.983
not being able to stand.

15:11.060 --> 15:14.078
I'm so lonely I made a Marge
from insulation.

15:14.155 --> 15:15.154
LISA:
Mommy?

15:15.231 --> 15:17.073
Bart and I decided
we'll give up

15:17.083 --> 15:19.992
all our toys for Christmas
if Daddy can come back.

15:20.069 --> 15:21.494
But I'll need double
on my birthday.

15:21.570 --> 15:22.828
Take it or leave it.

15:22.905 --> 15:24.914
What's happened to you?

15:24.925 --> 15:27.258
BART:
I'm becoming a jerk
because I have no dad.

15:27.335 --> 15:30.211
MARGE:
So you'll be better
if he comes back?

15:30.287 --> 15:33.097
BART:
Maybe not, but you won't get
all the blame.

15:33.174 --> 15:35.224
♪ ♪

15:41.590 --> 15:43.349
Well, I want him back, too.

15:43.426 --> 15:44.892
BOTH:
Yay!

15:44.969 --> 15:47.436
MARGE:
I want him back,
but I need your father

15:47.447 --> 15:49.355
to do one great thing.

15:49.432 --> 15:50.690
One thing to show

15:50.766 --> 15:53.192
that all the nonsense
I put up with has a point.

15:53.269 --> 15:54.944
Now, we're going to go
to midnight mass

15:54.955 --> 15:56.737
without your father.

15:56.814 --> 15:59.115
Aw, missing church.

15:59.125 --> 16:01.909
This is the saddest
I've ever been happy.

16:01.986 --> 16:03.744
(car departing)

16:03.821 --> 16:05.797
("O Holy Night" playing)

16:12.305 --> 16:14.806
One thing. One gesture.

16:14.882 --> 16:16.632
(gasps)
I know!

16:16.643 --> 16:20.428
I'll do the thing that Christmas
is really all about!

16:20.504 --> 16:22.605
Make cookies.

16:23.966 --> 16:25.641
Dad made cookies!

16:25.652 --> 16:26.651
Yay!

16:26.728 --> 16:27.935
How many did you eat?

16:28.012 --> 16:30.646
Most but not all.

16:30.657 --> 16:33.315
(gasps)
Oh, that's wonderful!

16:33.326 --> 16:34.701
Mwah.

16:36.145 --> 16:37.537
(gasping, shouting)

16:40.858 --> 16:43.284
(groans)
No forgiveness, no cookies,

16:43.360 --> 16:44.744
and I burned the good drapes

16:44.820 --> 16:47.246
so we'll have to get
corncob curtains.

16:47.323 --> 16:49.665
(sighs)
I need a miracle,

16:49.676 --> 16:51.834
but those never happen
at Christmas.

16:51.845 --> 16:53.511
(Maude groaning)

16:53.588 --> 16:55.337
MAUDE:
Contraction!

16:55.348 --> 16:58.516
Oh, if only that pregnant woman
would stop that racket

16:58.593 --> 16:59.851
so I could think.

16:59.927 --> 17:01.635
You<i> could deliver the baby.</i>

17:01.712 --> 17:02.636
Wait, who are you?

17:02.713 --> 17:03.804
<i> I'm your brain.</i>

17:03.881 --> 17:05.264
How come I haven't heard
from you before?

17:05.341 --> 17:07.308
<i> Your stomach gets all the bloo.</i>

17:07.384 --> 17:08.642
<i> You shut up about that!</i>

17:08.719 --> 17:10.102
<i> I know where you live.</i>

17:10.179 --> 17:11.854
Oh, the baby's coming.

17:11.865 --> 17:14.315
Oh, wh-where's your father?

17:14.391 --> 17:17.368
He's delivering
Christmas turkeys to the poor.

17:17.445 --> 17:19.028
That selfish jerk.

17:19.039 --> 17:21.947
Did somebody order
an unlikely hero?

17:22.024 --> 17:24.450
Maude, let's get you
to the hospital.

17:24.527 --> 17:25.543
(moans)
No.

17:25.620 --> 17:26.952
It's too late.

17:27.029 --> 17:30.039
Then I'll deliver this baby
myself.

17:30.050 --> 17:32.041
How are you gonna do that?

17:32.052 --> 17:33.667
The same way I learned

17:33.744 --> 17:36.378
what the top ten bass solos
through history are--

17:36.389 --> 17:38.222
through YouTube.

17:38.299 --> 17:41.559
("My Generation"
bass solo playing)

17:41.636 --> 17:44.345
Oh, there's always a commercial.

17:44.421 --> 17:47.231
There will be a time,
mark my words,

17:47.308 --> 17:50.860
where the monkey attempts
to eat your face.

17:54.765 --> 17:56.690
If you've done
everything correctly,

17:56.767 --> 17:59.527
your mother-to-be
is calm and peaceful.

17:59.603 --> 18:00.912
(groans)
Shut up.

18:00.988 --> 18:02.655
You know nothing.

18:02.731 --> 18:04.916
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to get angry.

18:04.992 --> 18:06.075
That's okay.

18:06.086 --> 18:07.418
Of course it's okay!

18:07.495 --> 18:08.536
(moans)

18:08.588 --> 18:09.912
Could you do me a favor?

18:09.923 --> 18:10.871
(grunts)

18:10.948 --> 18:11.914
Anything.

18:11.925 --> 18:12.998
Pretend to be Ned.

18:13.075 --> 18:14.667
(huffing)

18:14.743 --> 18:15.927
Okay.

18:16.003 --> 18:17.261
(stammering)

18:17.338 --> 18:18.453
Oodily doodily.

18:18.455 --> 18:20.923
Uh, no clownin',
that baby's crownin'.

18:20.934 --> 18:23.101
You're almost out of labor,
neighbor.

18:23.177 --> 18:25.678
No, no. The real Ned.

18:25.754 --> 18:28.097
Um, uh, uh,
I'm a left-handed weirdo

18:28.108 --> 18:29.765
with a cop mustache.

18:29.776 --> 18:31.725
No. No, no, no.
(moans)

18:31.802 --> 18:35.604
I mean the quiet,
wonderful man I married.

18:35.615 --> 18:36.614
All right.

18:36.691 --> 18:38.023
To help you deliver this baby,

18:38.100 --> 18:40.067
I'll make
the ultimate sacrifice.

18:40.144 --> 18:42.328
I'll act like a weenie.

18:43.439 --> 18:45.239
Maude, I know I'll love heaven

18:45.316 --> 18:47.408
because you've made one for me
on Earth.

18:47.484 --> 18:50.670
Let's bring another angel
into this world.

18:52.990 --> 18:54.707
Perfectly normal.

18:54.783 --> 18:57.793
Eight fingers and eight toes.

18:57.828 --> 18:58.961
Aw.

18:58.972 --> 19:00.379
How long have you been here?

19:00.456 --> 19:02.965
Long enough to see
the man I married

19:02.976 --> 19:05.301
is heroic and wise

19:05.311 --> 19:07.928
and capable and brave

19:08.005 --> 19:09.555
-and...
-Give me my baby!

19:09.632 --> 19:11.307
I guess it is mostly yours.

19:11.317 --> 19:12.391
Here.

19:12.468 --> 19:14.977
Homie, you did great.

19:14.988 --> 19:17.029
Mmm!

19:18.140 --> 19:19.315
Oh, Maude.

19:19.325 --> 19:20.482
I'm so sorry.

19:20.493 --> 19:21.492
It's okay, Neddy.

19:21.569 --> 19:23.402
I was in good hands.

19:23.479 --> 19:25.988
I redeemed myself at Christmas,

19:25.999 --> 19:27.165
like the Grinch,

19:27.241 --> 19:28.741
the<i> Die Hard</i> guy

19:28.817 --> 19:30.251
and<i> Scrooged.</i>

19:31.245 --> 19:32.620
In honor of today,

19:32.696 --> 19:35.080
we're gonna name our son Homer.

19:35.157 --> 19:36.123
-(grunts)
-Uh...

19:36.200 --> 19:37.666
Todd Homer Flanders.

19:37.677 --> 19:40.002
Todd's middle name is Homer?

19:40.013 --> 19:41.795
Yep. And for similar reasons,

19:41.872 --> 19:44.098
Maggie's middle name is Lenny.

19:45.334 --> 19:49.178
But that's a story
for the next Arbor Day.

19:49.189 --> 19:50.971
Well, I want to see
your secret room.

19:51.024 --> 19:52.765
Oh-oh-oh, not so fast, boy.

19:52.841 --> 19:55.267
First you have to tell me
one of<i> your</i> secrets.

19:55.344 --> 19:56.861
Okay. Not saying why,

19:56.938 --> 19:59.230
but you might want to get
a new toothbrush.

19:59.306 --> 20:00.981
(chuckles)

20:01.058 --> 20:02.441
You, too, son.

20:02.518 --> 20:03.492
You, too.

20:08.282 --> 20:10.950
And I found out something else
about the day you were born.

20:11.026 --> 20:12.451
What?

20:12.528 --> 20:14.662
You were born
with a full set of teeth.

20:14.738 --> 20:16.047
And here they are!

20:16.123 --> 20:18.216
(shrieking)

20:18.292 --> 20:19.717
GRAMPA:
Where are my dentures?!

20:19.794 --> 20:21.293
I got a hot date tonight,

20:21.370 --> 20:23.304
and I want to show off
by eatin' chicken.

20:25.040 --> 20:26.974
What am I doin' up there?

20:32.306 --> 20:33.898
(chuckling)

20:33.975 --> 20:35.900
(moaning)

20:38.554 --> 20:40.062
(chuckles)

20:40.073 --> 20:41.689
You think the kids can hear?

20:41.765 --> 20:44.233
No, no, everything up here
is totally soundproof.

20:44.244 --> 20:46.077
Well, don't let me stop youse.

